{"key":"post-16009239","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16009239</id>\n<content>I keep mine to 15 psi and below now.&amp;nbsp; For awhile I was sterilizing at up to 20 psi, but it was weakening the bags too much, leading to fatigue cracks and pinholes opening up.&amp;nbsp; That problem doesn't occur at 15 psi or less.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I generally use 90 to 120 minutes at 15 for large bags of grain. Alternatively, I can sterilize the grains in my &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Biomass-Powered-Steam-Generator&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;wood fired sterilizer&lt;/a&gt; for 8 hours.&amp;nbsp; We load up to 6 quarts in each bag, prepared as shown in the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Grain-Preparation&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;Grain prep chapter of Let's Grow Mushrooms&lt;/a&gt;.</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16021105</next>\n<prev>16008527</prev>\n<first>16006511</first>\n<last>16021105</last>\n<when>1332967130</when>\n<utime>03/28/12 11:38 PM</utime>\n</post>"}